---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { PARENT_BRAND, PARENT_SITE, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About PathAble Engineering"
  description="What this publication is, who maintains it, and how we work in the open."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About {SITE_TITLE}</h1>

    <p class="lede muted">
      {SITE_TITLE} is the public engineering publication of{' '}
      <a href={PARENT_SITE} rel="noopener">{PARENT_BRAND}</a> &mdash; a mission-driven
      studio building accessible, accountable, workflow-first software for the disability
      employment community.
    </p>

    <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
    <p>
      We publish technical articles, architecture notes, practice guides, and
      open-source documentation. This is a space for sharing how we build, the
      trade-offs we make, and the accessibility practices we hold ourselves to.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Synthetic examples only.</strong> We never publish protected health
        information, customer details, or sensitive implementation details. All examples
        are illustrative.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Accessible by default.</strong> Articles are reviewed for accessibility
        (semantics, contrast, alt text) before publication.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Honest about maturity.</strong> Work is clearly labeled as experimental,
        evolving, or stable.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No unsupported claims.</strong> We avoid overstating security, accessibility,
        or compliance guarantees.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Engineering vs. company website</h2>
    <p>
      This site is the canonical home for our technical writing. For company,
      product, services, and pilot-program information, visit{' '}
      <a href={PARENT_SITE} rel="noopener">pathableai.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Ownership &amp; review</h2>
    <p>
      Ownership and editorial review responsibilities are documented in the
      repository under <code>docs/editorial-and-ownership.md</code>. The
      generator and repository strategy are recorded in{' '}
      <code>docs/decision-records/</code>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
